iii) $\left|\frac{P}{Q}\right| = \left|\frac{Q}{P}\right| \rightarrow \text{True}
multiplicative inverse of fraction
Ex: P = (-2), Q = 3
\rightarrow \left|\frac{-2}{3}\right| = \left|\frac{3}{-2}\right| = \frac{2}{3} = \frac{3}{2} \text{ (multiplicative inverse)}

2\sqrt{3}x^2 - 5x + \sqrt{3} = 0
\Rightarrow 2\sqrt{3}x^2 - 3x - 2x + \sqrt{3} = 0
\Rightarrow \sqrt{3}x(2x - \sqrt{3}) - 1(2x - \sqrt{3}) = 0
\Rightarrow (\sqrt{3}x - 1)(2x - \sqrt{3}) = 0
So,
\alpha = \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} \text{ or } \frac{\sqrt{3}}{3}
\beta = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}
So,
Relations:-
i) \alpha + \beta = \frac{-b}{a}
LHS RHS
\frac{\sqrt{3}}{3} + \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \frac{-(-5)}{2\sqrt{3}}
\frac{2\sqrt{3} + 3\sqrt{3}}{6} \frac{5}{2\sqrt{3}}
Multiply \sqrt{3} n & d
\frac{5\sqrt{3}}{6} \frac{5}{2\sqrt{3}} \times \frac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}}
\frac{5\sqrt{3}}{6} = \frac{5\sqrt{3}}{6}
\alpha\beta = \frac{c}{a}
LHS RHS
\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} \times \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2\sqrt{3}}
\frac{1}{2} = \frac{1}{2} \text{ (HP)}

