LHS
\frac{\sqrt{3}}{3} + \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}
\frac{2\sqrt{3} + 3\sqrt{3}}{6}
RHS
\frac{-(-5)}{2\sqrt{3}}
\frac{5}{2\sqrt{3}}
\frac{5\sqrt{3}}{6}
Multiply \sqrt{3} n & d
\frac{5}{2\sqrt{3}} \times \frac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}} = \frac{5\sqrt{3}}{6}
\alpha\beta = \frac{c}{a}
