= \frac{1}{2} (HP)

Q13
3x^2 + 4x - 4
The '3' is coefficient of 'x^2' or '4' is coefficient of 'x', '-4' is constant.
3x^2 - 2x + 6x - 4
x(3x-2) + 2(3x-2)
(x+2)(3x-2)
x+2=0
x=-2
3x-2=0
x=\frac{2}{3}
\alpha + \beta = \frac{-b}{a}
\alpha \times \beta = \frac{c}{a}
a = 3
b = 4
c = -4
3 \times 4 = 12
-2 + \frac{2}{3} = \frac{-4}{3}
\frac{-4}{3} = \frac{-4}{3}
-2 \times \frac{2}{3} = \frac{-4}{3}
\frac{-4}{3} = \frac{-4}{3}

